executor_description: Resetting knowledge base settings to its defaults

Webhooks enable Groove to post data to your server whenever an event has happened. Webhooks can be thought of as event listeners of push notifications.  Webhooks can also be configured through the Groove user interface.
Replacing all labels on a ticket
Resetting widget settings to its defaults
Because our api limits messages to 25 attachments, you should check to make sure there are enough attachments remaining for the number of files you are preparing to upload.
You can send a single binary file, which is supported by most clients.
You can also run search requests against your knowledge base's default base URL (see "Settings" of your knowledge base).
